WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.805 --> 00:00:06.006
[ Saucer whirs ]

2
00:00:07.742 --> 00:00:09.611
-This the place?
-This the place.

3
00:00:11.345 --> 00:00:12.647
[ Grunts ]

4
00:00:12.680 --> 00:00:13.815
[ Machine beeps ]

5
00:00:13.848 --> 00:00:15.382
-This the stuff?
-This the stuff.

6
00:00:15.415 --> 00:00:17.251
And this is no ordinary stuff.
Morty.

7
00:00:17.284 --> 00:00:19.754
This sap is <i>primo</i> .

8
00:00:19.787 --> 00:00:21.523
[ Both grunting ]

9
00:00:21.556 --> 00:00:23.457
[ Liquid sloshes ]

10
00:00:23.490 --> 00:00:25.660
[ Vines creak ]

11
00:00:25.693 --> 00:00:26.995
-Argh!
-Ah!

12
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:28.997
-What the hell?
-Shit! Vines!

13
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:30.330
[ Both grunting ]

14
00:00:30.364 --> 00:00:34.101
Locusts come
to harvest my bounty.

15
00:00:34.134 --> 00:00:36.004
Hey. giant ancient tree guy.

16
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:38.372
Sorry. We thought
the sap was accountability free.

17
00:00:38.405 --> 00:00:41.576
Yeah. well. we're not locusts.
just a couple adventurers.

18
00:00:41.609 --> 00:00:43.845
Spacefarers.

19
00:00:43.878 --> 00:00:46.014
You consume your planets.

20
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:49.617
then spread your sickness
to the stars.

21
00:00:49.651 --> 00:00:51.986
Nah. Nah. man.
We're clean. I promise.

22
00:00:52.020 --> 00:00:53.220
Yeah. yeah.
We just got tested.

23
00:00:53.253 --> 00:00:55.155
and I got a bit of
a soy allergy.

24
00:00:55.188 --> 00:00:58.993
I have a place
for animals like you.

25
00:00:59.027 --> 00:01:02.764
You will be reformed.

26
00:01:02.797 --> 00:01:05.700
[ Groaning ]
[ Groaning ]

27
00:01:05.733 --> 00:01:07.602
What is...

28
00:01:07.635 --> 00:01:14.943
♪♪

29
00:01:14.976 --> 00:01:22.817
♪♪

30
00:01:22.850 --> 00:01:24.586
[ Water splashes ]

31
00:01:24.619 --> 00:01:26.086
...this?!

32
00:01:26.119 --> 00:01:27.387
Yeah. Morty.

33
00:01:27.421 --> 00:01:28.723
Not ideal.

34
00:01:28.756 --> 00:01:30.625
But I promise you.
the sap will be worth it.

35
00:01:30.658 --> 00:01:33.493
I had the craziest night
on this stuff a few weeks ago.

36
00:01:33.528 --> 00:01:43.504
♪♪

37
00:01:43.538 --> 00:01:52.580
♪♪

38
00:01:52.614 --> 00:02:01.221
♪♪

39
00:02:01.254 --> 00:02:03.490
[ Electricity hisses ]

40
00:02:05.258 --> 00:02:06.828
I'm all wobbly. Rick.

41
00:02:06.861 --> 00:02:07.962
What the fuck's going on.

42
00:02:07.996 --> 00:02:09.964
In the same position you are.

43
00:02:09.998 --> 00:02:11.866
But I can guess that those roots
extracted the biological data

44
00:02:11.899 --> 00:02:14.836
we think of as our minds
and reincarnated us as amoeba.

45
00:02:14.869 --> 00:02:16.604
How do we get our
old bodies back?

46
00:02:16.638 --> 00:02:18.506
Well.
that's the wrong question.

47
00:02:18.539 --> 00:02:20.675
But it's the one all
new cellmates ask.

48
00:02:20.708 --> 00:02:22.476
[ Laughs ] "Cellmates."

49
00:02:22.510 --> 00:02:24.712
We use humor to stay sane
in this place.

50
00:02:24.746 --> 00:02:26.179
Yes. sir.

51
00:02:26.213 --> 00:02:27.347
Many folks have tried
to raid this planet

52
00:02:27.381 --> 00:02:28.816
and ended up down here.

53
00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:30.217
Growth and rebirth.

54
00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:31.451
The ball and chain
around our ankles.

55
00:02:31.485 --> 00:02:33.888
In here. a man can truly change.

56
00:02:33.921 --> 00:02:35.923
But don't mistake that
for freedom.

57
00:02:35.957 --> 00:02:38.191
Give me your cytoplasm.
you limp-dick motherfucker!

58
00:02:38.225 --> 00:02:39.426
[ Yells ]

59
00:02:39.459 --> 00:02:40.460
[ Squish ]

60
00:02:40.494 --> 00:02:41.596
Argh!

61
00:02:41.629 --> 00:02:42.664
[ Grunts ]

62
00:02:42.697 --> 00:02:44.832
[ Slurps ]

63
00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:47.869
[ Water splashes ]

64
00:02:47.902 --> 00:02:49.137
What?
Huh.

65
00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.505
Guess if you die.
you start over.

66
00:02:50.538 --> 00:02:52.140
Good thing
we hadn't made much progress.

67
00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:53.473
Try not to die. Morty.

68
00:02:53.508 --> 00:02:54.842
Hello. my delicious friends.

69
00:02:54.876 --> 00:02:56.010
He's multicellular now!

70
00:02:56.044 --> 00:02:57.344
Back for
another helping?

71
00:02:57.377 --> 00:02:58.813
Spawn-camping piece of shit!

72
00:02:58.846 --> 00:03:00.380
[ Grunts. gurgles ]
Jesus!

73
00:03:00.414 --> 00:03:02.215
Prison rules. Morty.
Get to the top of the food chain

74
00:03:02.249 --> 00:03:03.584
or you're someone's dinner.

75
00:03:03.618 --> 00:03:05.019
[ Grunts. slurps ]

76
00:03:05.053 --> 00:03:06.521
Hey. get in here.
We need the nutrients.

77
00:03:06.554 --> 00:03:07.354
[ Slurps ]

78
00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:09.590
Oh. it's like salty tapioca.

79
00:03:09.624 --> 00:03:11.993
If this place is dumb enough
to let us manipulate our DNA.

80
00:03:12.026 --> 00:03:13.761
Morty. then we'll
just evolve our way out.

81
00:03:13.795 --> 00:03:14.929
First step is fins.

82
00:03:14.962 --> 00:03:17.197
Wait. How?
Mitosis. Morty.

83
00:03:17.230 --> 00:03:19.167
Think really hard
about being your own daughter.

84
00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:20.168
[ Grunts ]

85
00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:21.201
[ Grunts ]

86
00:03:21.234 --> 00:03:23.004
[ Grunting continues ]

87
00:03:23.037 --> 00:03:27.374
♪♪

88
00:03:27.407 --> 00:03:28.810
Being a fish isn't so bad.

89
00:03:28.843 --> 00:03:30.578
Swimming is fun.

90
00:03:30.611 --> 00:03:32.180
I do like
how you're never thirsty.

91
00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:33.948
And the whole world's
your toilet.

92
00:03:38.119 --> 00:03:40.088
[ Both gasping ]

93
00:03:40.121 --> 00:03:41.522
Oh. Oh. air.
[ Gasping ]

94
00:03:41.556 --> 00:03:42.389
So good.

95
00:03:42.422 --> 00:03:43.891
[ Strained ] So good.

96
00:03:44.759 --> 00:03:46.060
[ Snake hisses ]

97
00:03:46.094 --> 00:03:47.729
[ Animals growl ]

98
00:03:48.162 --> 00:03:49.362
[ Gasps ]

99
00:03:50.031 --> 00:03:50.998
[ Groans ]

100
00:03:51.032 --> 00:03:52.967
[ Breathing heavily ]

101
00:03:53.801 --> 00:03:55.268
Toughen up. Morty.

102
00:03:55.302 --> 00:03:56.637
The primordial soup was
just the beginning.

103
00:03:56.671 --> 00:03:58.238
We're in some kind of
hollow earth.

104
00:03:58.271 --> 00:04:00.340
The reincarnation field
must be contained

105
00:04:00.373 --> 00:04:01.809
within the warden's
root lattice.

106
00:04:01.843 --> 00:04:02.977
If we escape to the surface.

107
00:04:03.010 --> 00:04:04.045
we escape the cycle.

108
00:04:04.078 --> 00:04:05.146
[ Gasping ]

109
00:04:05.179 --> 00:04:06.547
[ Choking ]

110
00:04:06.581 --> 00:04:09.050
God damn it. Morty.
you're a lungfish.

111
00:04:09.083 --> 00:04:11.953
Use your lungs.

112
00:04:11.986 --> 00:04:13.453
[ Groans ]

113
00:04:14.622 --> 00:04:15.923
[ Groans ]

114
00:04:15.957 --> 00:04:17.992
[ Water burbles ]

115
00:04:20.628 --> 00:04:22.663
[ Orb whirs ]

116
00:04:25.133 --> 00:04:26.399
[ Water splashes ]

117
00:04:27.168 --> 00:04:28.703
Sorry.

118
00:04:28.736 --> 00:04:30.171
You know how much willpower
it takes to drown yourself?

119
00:04:30.204 --> 00:04:31.438
W-What do you want
to try next?

120
00:04:31.471 --> 00:04:33.741
I got eight words for you...

121
00:04:33.775 --> 00:04:35.743
legs.

122
00:04:35.777 --> 00:04:37.277
This is great.

123
00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:38.813
We let our food come to us
and plan our next move.

124
00:04:38.846 --> 00:04:40.648
Um. I think I'm stuck.

125
00:04:40.681 --> 00:04:41.849
In our own web?

126
00:04:41.883 --> 00:04:44.018
It's fine.
I'll use you and pull myself up.

127
00:04:44.051 --> 00:04:45.119
[ Stammers ] Don't!

128
00:04:45.153 --> 00:04:46.587
Oh!
Damn it!

129
00:04:46.621 --> 00:04:49.489
[ Chuckles ]
Not so fun. is it?

130
00:04:49.524 --> 00:04:51.424
Eat shit!
I'm gonna!

131
00:04:51.458 --> 00:04:53.360
Morty.
I'm gonna evolve wings.

132
00:04:53.393 --> 00:04:54.962
and then I'm gonna
kill that guy.

133
00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:56.697
[ Water splashes ]

134
00:04:56.731 --> 00:04:58.166
Morty: Whoo-hoo!

135
00:04:58.199 --> 00:04:59.901
This is amazing. Rick.

136
00:04:59.934 --> 00:05:01.269
And really quick to get to.

137
00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:03.738
Birds are basically
small dinosaurs.

138
00:05:03.771 --> 00:05:05.740
All right. Morty.
there's no thermals.

139
00:05:05.773 --> 00:05:08.276
So we've got to evolve really
specific wings to get up there.

140
00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:10.144
Oh. you can't build us
mech suits yet.

141
00:05:10.178 --> 00:05:11.712
Nah. birds can get
wherever they want.

142
00:05:11.746 --> 00:05:13.514
but can't do anything
once they get there.

143
00:05:13.548 --> 00:05:15.149
It's like astral projection.

144
00:05:15.183 --> 00:05:16.349
[ Squawks ]
Oh. shit!

145
00:05:16.383 --> 00:05:17.852
he can get us down here.
too.

146
00:05:17.885 --> 00:05:23.958
♪♪

147
00:05:23.991 --> 00:05:25.760
All right. Pretty obvious.

148
00:05:25.793 --> 00:05:27.261
We gotta climb a tech tree
to climb the actual tree.

149
00:05:27.295 --> 00:05:29.530
And we do that with...

150
00:05:29.564 --> 00:05:32.499
Hands. Supple. grippy hands

151
00:05:32.533 --> 00:05:34.302
and a pretty familiar version
of --

152
00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:37.171
God. just go already.
Don't wait up!

153
00:05:37.205 --> 00:05:39.006
[ Imitating monkey squalls ]

154
00:05:42.276 --> 00:05:45.279
Um. this watering hole is
pretty tense.

155
00:05:45.313 --> 00:05:48.516
Pretty. um. ape heavy.
Exactly.

156
00:05:48.549 --> 00:05:51.786
There's holes for apes only.
Clear out.

157
00:05:51.819 --> 00:05:54.354
Oh. we were just.
uh. drinking water.

158
00:05:54.387 --> 00:05:55.790
And using tools!

159
00:05:55.823 --> 00:05:58.693
Hey. look.
this guy's jerking off a stick

160
00:05:58.726 --> 00:05:59.794
with his rock

161
00:05:59.827 --> 00:06:01.229
He's a stick stroker!

162
00:06:01.262 --> 00:06:03.164
I'm gonna end you. tool man.

163
00:06:03.197 --> 00:06:05.166
We. uh. we-we-we
we can move along.

164
00:06:05.199 --> 00:06:06.399
Argh!

165
00:06:06.433 --> 00:06:07.969
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Groans ]

166
00:06:08.002 --> 00:06:09.337
Oh. my God. Rick!

167
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:10.504
Hey. what the fuck?
Hey! Kill those monkeys

168
00:06:10.538 --> 00:06:11.606
slightly different than us.

169
00:06:11.639 --> 00:06:13.473
What are you doing. Rick?

170
00:06:13.507 --> 00:06:15.910
They started it. Domination
through technology. Morty.

171
00:06:15.943 --> 00:06:18.980
We're going apex.
This stick is your god!

172
00:06:19.013 --> 00:06:20.047
He's got a thing!

173
00:06:20.081 --> 00:06:21.315
[ Grunts ]

174
00:06:21.349 --> 00:06:22.316
Oh!

175
00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:23.584
Ri... Rick?

176
00:06:23.618 --> 00:06:24.819
I'm doing this
for both of us.

177
00:06:24.852 --> 00:06:26.787
I'll find you
when I find you.

178
00:06:30.658 --> 00:06:32.459
Guess he really did bail
on me.

179
00:06:32.492 --> 00:06:33.527
You lost. son?

180
00:06:33.561 --> 00:06:35.395
Oh. Oh. hey. Uh. please --

181
00:06:35.428 --> 00:06:37.164
Please don't kill me
for my cytoplasm.

182
00:06:37.198 --> 00:06:38.699
Oh. child.

183
00:06:38.733 --> 00:06:41.468
you've been trapped in
the cycle of violence too long.

184
00:06:41.502 --> 00:06:43.504
I don't know.
maybe you're right.

185
00:06:43.537 --> 00:06:45.306
I'm tired of fighting
all the time.

186
00:06:45.339 --> 00:06:46.974
Mm-hmm.

187
00:06:47.008 --> 00:06:49.543
I've seen countless souls
waste a billion lifetimes trying

188
00:06:49.577 --> 00:06:51.178
to bust out of here.

189
00:06:51.212 --> 00:06:52.780
But you can't fight
the cycle. son.

190
00:06:52.813 --> 00:06:55.482
You got to submit to it.
Serve nature.

191
00:06:55.516 --> 00:06:57.985
Is this where you kill me?

192
00:06:58.019 --> 00:07:00.354
Oh. you are traumatized.

193
00:07:00.388 --> 00:07:06.627
♪♪

194
00:07:06.661 --> 00:07:07.929
Wow!

195
00:07:07.962 --> 00:07:09.563
Pollinating. building
little hexagon houses.

196
00:07:09.597 --> 00:07:11.332
feels good to do
something positive.

197
00:07:11.365 --> 00:07:12.333
All: Mm-hmm.

198
00:07:12.366 --> 00:07:13.734
You see?

199
00:07:13.768 --> 00:07:15.069
And I reckon the warden
likes it. too.

200
00:07:15.102 --> 00:07:16.871
What are you in for. Morty?

201
00:07:16.904 --> 00:07:19.907
I was a scout for an orc species
looking for planets to conquer.

202
00:07:19.941 --> 00:07:22.109
I was a scout
for a sludge species looking

203
00:07:22.143 --> 00:07:23.544
for planets to conquer.

204
00:07:23.577 --> 00:07:25.713
Well. I'm a touch different

205
00:07:25.746 --> 00:07:29.917
because I was a pod person
looking for planets to conquer.

206
00:07:29.951 --> 00:07:32.386
I was helping
my grandpa get sap.

207
00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:34.388
I assume it makes energy
or gets you high.

208
00:07:34.422 --> 00:07:35.890
I-I-I don't know.

209
00:07:35.923 --> 00:07:37.792
Aha. That adds up.

210
00:07:37.825 --> 00:07:40.928
He seems the type to be
locked in here. but you don't.

211
00:07:40.962 --> 00:07:42.029
Thank you!

212
00:07:42.063 --> 00:07:44.432
It's a... There's a...

213
00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:47.201
G-O-R...

214
00:07:48.202 --> 00:07:52.239
Should've... spelled... "ape."

215
00:07:52.273 --> 00:07:53.641
[ Water splashes ]

216
00:07:53.674 --> 00:07:55.076
On to the next one.

217
00:07:55.109 --> 00:07:57.445
Every cycle evolves
as closer to parole.

218
00:07:57.477 --> 00:08:00.081
[ Cheering ]

219
00:08:00.114 --> 00:08:03.784
Ohhhh. I'm so fucking wounded.

220
00:08:03.818 --> 00:08:05.152
Everyone follow my lead.
Owwww.

221
00:08:05.186 --> 00:08:06.887
Your lead?
I'm the alpha.

222
00:08:06.921 --> 00:08:08.189
Dog. I'm the alpha.

223
00:08:08.222 --> 00:08:11.225
Easy prey here.
Easy pickings.

224
00:08:11.258 --> 00:08:12.259
Get em.
Now!

225
00:08:12.293 --> 00:08:14.862
I'm the alpha.
Omega!

226
00:08:14.895 --> 00:08:17.098
A hole? This isn't alpha at all.

227
00:08:17.131 --> 00:08:20.835
We're all betas now.
Come on. time to meet the boss.

228
00:08:20.868 --> 00:08:24.071
♪♪

229
00:08:24.105 --> 00:08:27.274
Hey. I know usually I'd
be trying to eat you and all.

230
00:08:27.308 --> 00:08:28.843
but maybe Los Lobos in the herd.

231
00:08:28.876 --> 00:08:31.345
Hey!
No interspecies solidarity.

232
00:08:31.379 --> 00:08:36.717
♪♪

233
00:08:36.751 --> 00:08:38.719
The wolves have
been incorporated. sir.

234
00:08:38.753 --> 00:08:40.888
All except for that one.

235
00:08:40.921 --> 00:08:43.357
I'm sorry for those things
I said about apes.

236
00:08:43.391 --> 00:08:45.226
More fermented berry mash.

237
00:08:45.259 --> 00:08:48.162
Right away. sir.
It's time to climb this fucker.

238
00:08:48.195 --> 00:08:49.997
♪♪

239
00:08:50.031 --> 00:08:51.699
[ Metal clangs ]

240
00:08:52.266 --> 00:08:53.502
[ Liquid hisses ]

241
00:08:53.534 --> 00:08:55.002
Listen up. pawns.

242
00:08:55.036 --> 00:08:57.104
We begin the task
of scaling this root.

243
00:08:57.138 --> 00:09:00.007
The root will kill you
if you touch it.

244
00:09:00.041 --> 00:09:02.877
You will go one at a time
for observation purposes.

245
00:09:02.910 --> 00:09:04.311
On. now.

246
00:09:04.345 --> 00:09:06.747
Kind of feel like I'm
being punished for my loyalty.

247
00:09:06.781 --> 00:09:08.549
Lead by example.
Gorilla #3.

248
00:09:08.582 --> 00:09:13.554
♪♪

249
00:09:13.587 --> 00:09:19.393
♪♪

250
00:09:19.427 --> 00:09:21.429
[ Gas hisses ]

251
00:09:21.462 --> 00:09:23.030
[ Groans ]

252
00:09:24.165 --> 00:09:25.499
Gas 20 feet up.

253
00:09:25.534 --> 00:09:27.034
Next!

254
00:09:29.170 --> 00:09:31.205
[ Distant screams ]

255
00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:34.275
[ Yells ]

256
00:09:34.308 --> 00:09:38.479
♪♪

257
00:09:38.513 --> 00:09:39.847
You know what? Fine.

258
00:09:39.880 --> 00:09:42.216
If we can't break out.
we break him.

259
00:09:42.249 --> 00:09:49.223
♪♪

260
00:09:49.256 --> 00:09:55.963
♪♪

261
00:09:55.996 --> 00:09:58.032
[ Vines creak ]

262
00:09:59.834 --> 00:10:00.868
Ugh!

263
00:10:00.901 --> 00:10:04.438
♪♪

264
00:10:04.472 --> 00:10:06.707
[ Fire hisses ]

265
00:10:07.608 --> 00:10:09.578
[ Thunder cracks ]

266
00:10:09.610 --> 00:10:14.415
♪♪

267
00:10:14.448 --> 00:10:16.083
[ Grunts ]

268
00:10:17.552 --> 00:10:19.420
[ Soft music plays ]

269
00:10:19.453 --> 00:10:22.123
So we clean shit
from the ocean?

270
00:10:22.156 --> 00:10:23.757
Ocean needs cleanin'.

271
00:10:25.426 --> 00:10:27.562
And we shit in the ocean?

272
00:10:27.596 --> 00:10:29.163
Ocean needs shittin'.

273
00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:36.804
And we shit in the soil while
eating shit out of the soil?

274
00:10:36.837 --> 00:10:39.340
You're pretty hung up on
the shit part of it. aren't you?

275
00:10:39.373 --> 00:10:44.245
♪♪

276
00:10:44.278 --> 00:10:45.946
What's troubling you. son?

277
00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:48.682
I mean. I like the
nonviolence. don't get me wrong.

278
00:10:48.716 --> 00:10:50.718
And having a shell is fun.

279
00:10:50.751 --> 00:10:53.053
but it just feels
like we're going in circles.

280
00:10:53.087 --> 00:10:55.624
Well. that's what
a healthy ecosystem is.

281
00:10:55.656 --> 00:10:57.391
Eventually. the warden
will notice

282
00:10:57.424 --> 00:10:59.026
our piety and set us free.

283
00:10:59.059 --> 00:11:01.862
Until then.
we find peace in here.

284
00:11:01.896 --> 00:11:04.665
So a reformed prisoner
is someone

285
00:11:04.698 --> 00:11:06.433
who doesn't want to leave
the prison?

286
00:11:06.467 --> 00:11:08.135
See? You get it.

287
00:11:08.169 --> 00:11:11.205
Oh. now you're probably
just hungry. Here.

288
00:11:11.238 --> 00:11:13.307
I guess I don't want to eat.
whoever that is.

289
00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:15.676
Now. son.
that's a vegetable.

290
00:11:15.709 --> 00:11:17.878
No one picks being a vegetable.

291
00:11:17.912 --> 00:11:21.916
you'd have to really give up
to be one of those.

292
00:11:21.949 --> 00:11:24.818
Hey. uh. I think
I'm maybe gonna brave the rest

293
00:11:24.852 --> 00:11:26.854
of this life alone.

294
00:11:26.887 --> 00:11:28.623
Well.
you know where to find us.

295
00:11:28.657 --> 00:11:30.157
We'll be eating shit.

296
00:11:30.191 --> 00:11:37.566
♪♪

297
00:11:37.599 --> 00:11:39.700
[ Water thuds ]

298
00:11:41.001 --> 00:11:43.003
[ Sighs ]

299
00:11:43.037 --> 00:11:44.606
[ Grunts ]

300
00:11:44.639 --> 00:11:48.075
♪♪

301
00:11:48.108 --> 00:11:49.210
Hmm.

302
00:11:49.243 --> 00:11:54.415
♪♪

303
00:11:54.448 --> 00:11:55.449
Oh.

304
00:11:55.482 --> 00:12:01.455
♪♪

305
00:12:01.488 --> 00:12:06.827
♪♪

306
00:12:06.860 --> 00:12:09.531
[ Shivering ]

307
00:12:09.564 --> 00:12:16.470
♪♪

308
00:12:16.504 --> 00:12:18.339
[ Laughing ]

309
00:12:18.372 --> 00:12:26.648
♪♪

310
00:12:26.681 --> 00:12:35.122
♪♪

311
00:12:35.155 --> 00:12:36.323
[ Farts ]

312
00:12:36.357 --> 00:12:41.228
♪♪

313
00:12:41.262 --> 00:12:42.463
[ Farts ]

314
00:12:42.496 --> 00:12:49.236
♪♪

315
00:12:49.270 --> 00:12:56.010
♪♪

316
00:12:56.043 --> 00:13:02.584
♪♪

317
00:13:02.617 --> 00:13:09.356
♪♪

318
00:13:09.390 --> 00:13:10.692
[ Grunts ]

319
00:13:10.725 --> 00:13:13.260
♪♪

320
00:13:13.294 --> 00:13:16.330
[ Gasps ] Sun! Real sun!

321
00:13:16.363 --> 00:13:18.098
[ Snoring ]

322
00:13:18.132 --> 00:13:21.135
Oh. great Warden! I did it!
I figured it out!

323
00:13:21.168 --> 00:13:24.171
The goal is to be a plant.
like you!

324
00:13:24.204 --> 00:13:25.839
Oh...
Whoa.

325
00:13:25.873 --> 00:13:27.875
So many nutrients in the soil
up here.

326
00:13:27.908 --> 00:13:29.410
Y-Yes.
[ Clears throat ]

327
00:13:29.443 --> 00:13:33.947
The life cycles of
the guilty provide nourishment.

328
00:13:33.981 --> 00:13:35.082
Oh.

329
00:13:35.115 --> 00:13:36.751
But that's
more of a byproduct

330
00:13:36.785 --> 00:13:38.753
than the point of all this.
right?

331
00:13:38.787 --> 00:13:41.723
[ Chuckles ]

332
00:13:41.756 --> 00:13:45.392
So I-I live up here now?

333
00:13:45.426 --> 00:13:48.697
Oh. uh.
this is my spot.

334
00:13:48.730 --> 00:13:52.099
Okay. I-I ca-- I can go
find my own planet.

335
00:13:52.132 --> 00:13:54.034
Ahhh.

336
00:13:54.068 --> 00:13:57.572
You would kinda need to be
a spacefarer for that.

337
00:13:57.605 --> 00:13:59.139
And I don't like those.

338
00:13:59.173 --> 00:14:02.142
But now you know
how cool it is to be a tree.

339
00:14:02.176 --> 00:14:04.144
Oh.
Boink!

340
00:14:04.178 --> 00:14:11.418
♪♪

341
00:14:11.452 --> 00:14:18.359
♪♪

342
00:14:18.392 --> 00:14:21.128
Okay. we have that
bronze post-mortem in 10.

343
00:14:21.161 --> 00:14:24.365
followed by the all hands
on opposable thumbs.

344
00:14:24.398 --> 00:14:26.668
[ Whistle! ]

345
00:14:26.701 --> 00:14:28.402
[ Thud! ]

346
00:14:30.471 --> 00:14:32.005
I'll reschedule.

347
00:14:33.907 --> 00:14:35.075
Look who it is.

348
00:14:35.109 --> 00:14:36.711
You don't have to do this.
man.

349
00:14:36.745 --> 00:14:39.012
The system's rigged. H-He
wants us fighting each other.

350
00:14:39.046 --> 00:14:41.816
Sounds like I'm on the
right side of history.
Morty!

351
00:14:41.850 --> 00:14:43.317
[ Grunting ]

352
00:14:43.350 --> 00:14:44.819
Alright. Morty.
let's shake a leg.

353
00:14:44.853 --> 00:14:46.220
When he respawns
in a second.

354
00:14:46.253 --> 00:14:47.689
he's not gonna be
any less annoying.

355
00:14:47.722 --> 00:14:49.123
Rick?!
Is this a coincidence?

356
00:14:49.156 --> 00:14:50.825
Y-You died
at the same time as me?

357
00:14:50.859 --> 00:14:52.527
I saw everything.
buddy.

358
00:14:52.560 --> 00:14:53.961
You beat the system.
then the system beat back.

359
00:14:53.994 --> 00:14:55.830
Ugh!
He's -- He's evil. Rick!

360
00:14:55.864 --> 00:14:57.665
He's feeding off the cycle
of death!

361
00:14:57.699 --> 00:14:59.768
W-We're all just mulch!

362
00:14:59.801 --> 00:15:01.902
Damn.
Pretty diabolical tree.

363
00:15:01.935 --> 00:15:04.639
I don't wanna be mulch!
I wanna go home!

364
00:15:04.672 --> 00:15:05.840
We have to stop killing
each other!

365
00:15:05.874 --> 00:15:07.474
We will. buddy.

366
00:15:07.509 --> 00:15:09.544
No more death now.
That's what feeds the tree.

367
00:15:09.577 --> 00:15:11.813
I'm back!
[ Grunts ]

368
00:15:11.846 --> 00:15:15.249
After that.
Now let's go.

369
00:15:15.282 --> 00:15:19.486
NAAAAAAAAAAAANTS
ingonyamaaaaa bagithi baba...

370
00:15:19.521 --> 00:15:21.422
[ Coughs ]

371
00:15:21.455 --> 00:15:23.157
Thanks for indulging me.

372
00:15:23.190 --> 00:15:25.959
I'm not in the form of a lion.
but I did want to sing the song.

373
00:15:25.993 --> 00:15:27.896
Hello. inmates.
[ Booing ]

374
00:15:27.928 --> 00:15:29.898
Okay. I deserve that.

375
00:15:29.930 --> 00:15:31.365
But I have something to say.

376
00:15:31.398 --> 00:15:33.802
You expect us
to listen to you?!

377
00:15:33.835 --> 00:15:37.672
No. I expect you
to listen to Morty.

378
00:15:37.705 --> 00:15:40.941
The Warden seems wise and stoic.
but he's just a big tree.

379
00:15:40.974 --> 00:15:42.877
Which means we can starve him
out!

380
00:15:42.911 --> 00:15:45.212
It's a hunger strike!
But for him.

381
00:15:45.245 --> 00:15:48.616
We'll all live peacefully
in a contained system.

382
00:15:48.650 --> 00:15:50.951
So instead of escaping.

383
00:15:50.984 --> 00:15:53.588
we'll live in a smaller.
shittier prison?

384
00:15:53.621 --> 00:15:54.589
I didn't say shittier!

385
00:15:54.622 --> 00:15:56.089
Gorilla 3. is that you?

386
00:15:56.123 --> 00:15:58.860
It's Hyena 3 now.
I got a new job.

387
00:15:58.893 --> 00:16:00.260
Seems like
a lateral step.

388
00:16:00.294 --> 00:16:02.396
Th-Think of it more
as a biodome.

389
00:16:02.429 --> 00:16:05.132
You've spent a million
lifetimes being dogs and fish.

390
00:16:05.165 --> 00:16:07.902
It won't kill you
to spend one lifetime on this.

391
00:16:07.936 --> 00:16:11.606
Hopefully nothing will kill you.
That's the point of the strike.

392
00:16:11.639 --> 00:16:13.741
[ All murmuring ]

393
00:16:13.775 --> 00:16:19.179
♪♪

394
00:16:19.213 --> 00:16:22.817
Oh. this was a mistake.
What? This looks great!

395
00:16:22.851 --> 00:16:25.486
Then again.
I am a bat.

396
00:16:25.520 --> 00:16:27.287
Welcome to ME!

397
00:16:27.321 --> 00:16:28.957
Combined with Morty's
plant-based livin'.

398
00:16:28.989 --> 00:16:30.959
we should all age
pretty gracefully.

399
00:16:30.991 --> 00:16:32.894
All he needs from you is...

400
00:16:32.927 --> 00:16:34.461
Hey. Mornin'.

401
00:16:34.495 --> 00:16:37.197
Shittin' hard
or hardly shittin'?
[ Laughs ]

402
00:16:37.231 --> 00:16:39.233
Ya know. when they pitched me
on this herbivore diet.

403
00:16:39.266 --> 00:16:41.836
I was skeptical.
but then I tried the pizza.

404
00:16:41.870 --> 00:16:43.771
[ Both laugh ]

405
00:16:43.805 --> 00:16:51.311
♪♪

406
00:16:51.345 --> 00:16:58.620
♪♪

407
00:16:58.653 --> 00:17:05.960
♪♪

408
00:17:05.994 --> 00:17:13.100
♪♪

409
00:17:13.133 --> 00:17:14.836
I need 34 bruschettas.
all day.

410
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:16.270
Yes. Chimp!

411
00:17:17.337 --> 00:17:19.139
And you laugh
at all my jokes.

412
00:17:19.172 --> 00:17:22.442
It's true. it's true.

413
00:17:22.476 --> 00:17:24.444
I led us all down here
with the expressed purpose

414
00:17:24.478 --> 00:17:26.446
of killing our tree
warden overlord.

415
00:17:26.480 --> 00:17:28.650
which I remind you is
still our goal.

416
00:17:28.683 --> 00:17:30.450
He should actually be
pretty weak by now.

417
00:17:30.484 --> 00:17:33.420
However. I knew we were putting
down roots.

418
00:17:33.453 --> 00:17:35.389
but never imagined
love would bloom.

419
00:17:35.422 --> 00:17:37.491
What doesn't bloom
down here?

420
00:17:37.525 --> 00:17:38.893
[ Laughter ]

421
00:17:38.927 --> 00:17:41.529
Ha ha ha. congratulations!

422
00:17:41.563 --> 00:17:44.064
Hyena 3 and Sheep.
you may now --

423
00:17:44.097 --> 00:17:46.834
Okay. already doing it.
Hot.

424
00:17:46.868 --> 00:17:49.136
[ Cheering ]

425
00:17:49.169 --> 00:17:51.573
Ho-ho. let's par-tay!

426
00:17:51.606 --> 00:17:55.610
[ Cheering ]

427
00:17:58.613 --> 00:18:00.080
Ohhh.

428
00:18:00.113 --> 00:18:03.885
I'm so...hungry.

429
00:18:03.918 --> 00:18:07.622
Wh-What's happening down there?

430
00:18:09.489 --> 00:18:13.493
Hey! Start killing each other!

431
00:18:13.528 --> 00:18:17.599
Hello? Anybody?

432
00:18:17.632 --> 00:18:21.368
Oh. you little fuckers
are gonna get it now!

433
00:18:32.479 --> 00:18:34.916
"Get bent."

434
00:18:34.949 --> 00:18:37.852
Get bent?
Little toothless.

435
00:18:37.885 --> 00:18:39.286
Not that I can beat it.

436
00:18:39.319 --> 00:18:40.487
Now!

437
00:18:41.789 --> 00:18:43.057
Aaaaah!

438
00:18:43.091 --> 00:18:45.026
[ Grunting ]

439
00:18:45.059 --> 00:18:49.797
♪♪

440
00:18:49.831 --> 00:18:52.232
It's working. He's too weak
to get us with his vines!

441
00:18:52.265 --> 00:18:54.736
Good thing. too.
I didn't anticipate how old

442
00:18:54.769 --> 00:18:57.437
and pacified our forces would be
by the time this plan worked.

443
00:18:57.471 --> 00:18:59.741
Come on. Hyena 3.
marriage made ya soft.

444
00:18:59.774 --> 00:19:02.710
Leave him alone!
You were always a toxic boss!

445
00:19:03.711 --> 00:19:05.345
[ Grunts ]

446
00:19:05.379 --> 00:19:07.915
It's working! Phase 2 now!

447
00:19:07.949 --> 00:19:14.088
♪♪

448
00:19:14.122 --> 00:19:20.427
♪♪

449
00:19:20.460 --> 00:19:21.562
Pull!

450
00:19:21.596 --> 00:19:23.430
[ All grunting ]

451
00:19:23.463 --> 00:19:24.766
♪♪

452
00:19:24.799 --> 00:19:25.967
No!

453
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:29.369
This planet was
my retirement!

454
00:19:29.403 --> 00:19:31.072
Say it with me. animals!

455
00:19:31.105 --> 00:19:33.574
All: Timber!

456
00:19:33.608 --> 00:19:38.211
♪♪

457
00:19:39.681 --> 00:19:44.652
[ Weakly ] Doesn't anybody hate
anybody anymore?

458
00:19:44.686 --> 00:19:49.157
Hey. birds. don't snakes
always eat your eggs?

459
00:19:49.189 --> 00:19:50.725
Don't --
Don't fall for that.

460
00:19:50.758 --> 00:19:54.128
Come on.
Someone's gotta have a grudge.

461
00:19:54.162 --> 00:19:56.130
This is too reformed!

462
00:19:56.164 --> 00:19:58.432
Oh. did we evolve
too much?

463
00:19:58.465 --> 00:20:02.770
I-I actually have
deep respect for spacefarers.

464
00:20:02.804 --> 00:20:05.773
Parked your ships all nice
and neat up there.

465
00:20:08.042 --> 00:20:09.777
If it makes you feel
any better.

466
00:20:09.811 --> 00:20:12.547
I didn't steal anything
from the glove boxes!

467
00:20:12.580 --> 00:20:18.986
No! I'm dying!
Plants rule...

468
00:20:19.020 --> 00:20:21.689
[ Cheering ]

469
00:20:24.859 --> 00:20:26.894
So...that --
that's it. then?

470
00:20:26.928 --> 00:20:30.765
I kinda thought we'd be returned
to our original bodies.

471
00:20:30.798 --> 00:20:33.701
No. no. no. no. we will.
We all just gotta believe.

472
00:20:33.735 --> 00:20:36.303
Yeah. we all just gotta
close our eyes.

473
00:20:36.336 --> 00:20:40.240
Mm. okay.
You guys got us this far.

474
00:20:48.415 --> 00:20:50.218
I don't feel anything.
Is it happening?

475
00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:51.886
Oh. it totally is.

476
00:20:51.919 --> 00:20:54.354
Ya gotta -- Ya gotta
keep those eyes tight. though.

477
00:20:54.387 --> 00:20:55.823
You sound farther away.

478
00:20:55.857 --> 00:20:58.425
Ohh! My leaf became a hand!
It's working!

479
00:20:58.458 --> 00:21:00.194
Hope that happens
to me.

480
00:21:00.228 --> 00:21:02.429
Rick: Whoa! Yeah! Ohhhh.

481
00:21:02.462 --> 00:21:06.399
Oh. ho. oh. it's so magical.

482
00:21:07.869 --> 00:21:11.239
Interesting how it happened
to them first.

483
00:21:11.271 --> 00:21:14.041
-Yeah!
-Hoo. hoo. hoo!

484
00:21:16.276 --> 00:21:18.445
[ Both sigh ]

485
00:21:18.478 --> 00:21:20.480
Where have you two been
all day?

486
00:21:20.515 --> 00:21:22.784
Nunya.
What's that? Biology?

487
00:21:22.817 --> 00:21:25.887
I think I know a thing
or two about that.

488
00:21:28.523 --> 00:21:29.289
Nope.

489
00:21:29.322 --> 00:21:37.098
♪♪

490
00:21:37.131 --> 00:21:44.939
♪♪

491
00:21:44.972 --> 00:21:52.747
♪♪

492
00:21:52.780 --> 00:22:00.621
♪♪

493
00:22:03.958 --> 00:22:06.426
Op! Excuse us.
Huh.

494
00:22:06.459 --> 00:22:08.629
Dude.
That was totally Hyena #3.

495
00:22:08.663 --> 00:22:10.363
Guess people got out.
huh?

496
00:22:10.397 --> 00:22:12.867
That is not
how I pictured him looking.

497
00:22:12.900 --> 00:22:14.602
Thanks. hon.

498
00:22:14.635 --> 00:22:17.605
This might sound crazy. but do
you know who I think I just saw?

499
00:22:17.638 --> 00:22:19.674
Was it the old man and boy
who saved us from prison

500
00:22:19.707 --> 00:22:22.143
but also left us trapped
in our animal bodies?

501
00:22:22.176 --> 00:22:23.978
You always fucking
step on my stories.
